<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="406" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d406">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">868.151/125</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Greece</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 307</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Athens</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-12">July 12, 1934</date>.<lb/>[Received August
                                    14.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: In reference to the Department’s
                                telegram No. 42 of July 6, 3 p.m. and my reply No. 70 of July 11, 10
                                a.m., I have the pleasure to report that during my absence from
                                Athens on a leave of short duration, the matter in question was
                                handled by Mr. Gade, Secretary of Legation, acting as Chargé
                                d’Affaires a. i. He requested and obtained <pb facs="0588" n="512" xml:id="pg_512"/> a personal interview with the Foreign
                                Minister, as suggested in the Department’s telegram, and secured the
                                postponement desired without the necessity of invoking the serious
                                view which the American Government would take of any arbitrary
                                action by the Greek Government at this time.</p>
                            <p>Respectfully yours,</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lincoln
                                MacVeagh</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>